          <p class='first-para'>
            I certainly did not say that full implementation of the information consultation directive would lead to consultation
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_119gc' title='Col. 119GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 March 2004 vol 659 c119GC' name='column_119gc' href='#column_119gc' rel='bookmark'>119GC</a>
            about directors' pay by the employees. I do not believe that it does, but I will check and, if I am wrong, I will come back to the noble Lord. I am afraid that I did not understand his second point about the reasons for employees being involved. Could he repeat it?
          </p>
