            All I would really like to say in relation to the points made by the noble Baroness, Lady Noakes. is that she postulates the idea of auditors who are not very good and a board that is not very good. However. what we are doing in the Bill is assuming&#x2014;-I think rightly&#x2014;that the auditors know, accept and embrace audit standards, and that the board of a company behaves as a board should behave. We are continuing to come back to how we define "reasonableness" and "awareness", how we establish a direct "need to know" in relation to the auditor, and what the auditor needs to know in relation to the board. Those are issues that we have been teasing out this afternoon, and we shall probably continue to tease them out for the next half hour and into Monday. They contribute to words that we shall all be reading over the next week or so.
